{"word":"κατάντης","slug":"κατάντης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατάντης</b></el> <el>(κατ-άντης, ες) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄντα'><el>ἄντα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>down-hill, downward, steep</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>εἰς τὸ κάταντες</el> <i>downwards</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>prone, inclined</i>, <el>πρός τι</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}